Some will come into your life even if expected but may or may not be welcomed. People will leave in real life too. Some may die, some may move one, sometimes you know why and sometimes you don’t. People can and do say things on social media that they probably would not do in real life. I am always impressed with the quality and character of those who even given the opportunity to remain unknown, choose to act with dignity and class. Those are the ones I will choose to follow. Those are the type of people I would want to be friends with in real life too!

question: Hi Lisa! Stumbled upon your blog last year and you are someone I look up to-- woohoo, women in games! I'm a lead designer at a small studio and have designing games for mobile for 2 years now. What are your thoughts on transitioning from mobile game design to AAA game design in terms of the kind of
answer: Aw, thanks! ^_^ (Oh God I really need to update my wordpress theme if people are stumbling upon my blog! :O).Also your question got cut off so I don't know the terms you were going to define, but I'll just take a best guess. Also note that having never been a designer on mobile games I'm speaking from one end of the spectrum here, but I do have a case study for you. My friend, David Shaver, transitioned from working primarily on mobile and casual games to becoming a designer at Respawn on Titanfall, so it is quite possible to do! However, most of what he did to sharpen up his AAA design skills to a quality level was done in his spare time on side projects. You can check that out here:  asked Dave for some words of wisdom on making the transition. Here's a summary of what he told me:1. Work your butt off on the side to build high quality work for the portfolio that demonstrates AAA skillset2. "Jack of all trades" skillsets, in his opinion, were more valued in mobile whereas AAA seeks out specialists. This isn't true of all places (Insomniac has more general designers, for example), but it certainly helps to be able to demonstrate a specific skillset (level design, combat, systems design, etc).3. Networking is important, and the mobile and AAA spheres can be a little different, so go out of your way to network with AAA folks.I'd say the skills you need in AAA depends on the types of games you want to work on, and then just being able to show off those skills, be that combat or quest design or whatever. I think whatever you're looking to get into, it's going to require supplemental portfolio work.I hope that answers the question! If it didn't, please feel free to follow-up :)

question: dear girls_  fill in the blank ? message to girls a
answer: dear girls of the worldhey! first off want to let you know that you're amazing in so many different ways, but if you don't think you are, then it's time to find those amazing things about you. just remember there's a difference between not knowing how you're amazing and a difference in ignoring them. dress confidently, even when you're alone. you'll feel powerful, feel all the power and pass you really have. it's going to be a magnificent day day because you can make a difference. whether it's just a difference you make for yourself, one other person, or for the whole world.you're young! hey, are you in college or already working every day? you're still young! do something crazy when you don't have work. be a little bit careless on your days off, but take work seriously. make goals for yourself. remind yourself that being over 1 doesn't mean you can't have fun if you don't manage your time. think of something you want to do or wanted to do. do it. take the steps to get there. little by little, with a little determination and positivity, you'll get there.don't call yourself fat or ugly 'cause you want your partner to feel pity for you and tell you you aren't. and don't think that if your partner doesn't compliment you everyday that s/he doesn't love you. same thing with parents; sometimes it's hard, but if they give you food, water, and stay by your side even when you're being bad, then be grateful. be grateful if you have siblings, and don't make them your enemies.things get hard. so hard that we just want to get up and scream to everybody or just kill ourselves. it's okay. everybody feels that in different ways in different times of life. you won't feel strong, but you are strong. just take it ten seconds at a time. 1..a..3..a..a..a..7..a..9..10.. you can do this. remind yourself there is so much you still want to see in the future...like your favorite band in concert! or that movie that's coming out in two years!don't be jealous. remember the good things of your life, but don't keep in negativity. sing, dance, and treat your body right because you never know when you'll lose it, and if you do, all you'll think about is how you didn't use it the way you should have. be humble and learn to be nice to the people that give love and care to you, not just the strangers you meet. don't think that you'll always have everything...or something.take bad people out of your life. teach people that they have to respect a fair lady like you. don't let anyone disrespect you, especially your partner or child. try not to be a bad person; don't be a bad person at all. learn from your mistakes and remember we all make mistakes.don't be afraid to love what you love. don't try to like something or support something 'cause everyone else does. learn to love and appreciate yourself before you ask anyone to love and support you. be yourself because you are extraordinary and unique.

question: would you be willing to lie to a court for a close friend if it meant saving your friend from going to jail for life??  bow your previous answer was too good @gaurav pain
answer: if my friend is potentially going to jail for life, then it's likely that they did something incredibly heinous. i'm also assuming that they're guilty since the question implies that i would have to lie in order to spoke holes in the prosecution's case. i wouldn't lie to save my friend from going to jail for life if there's good reason to believe that they committed a horrible crime that carries a life sentence. first of all, i'm not about to commit perjury and put myself in danger of getting hauled off to jail as well. second, i'm not going to deprive a victim or their family of receiving justice and closure. third, if my friend committed a violent crime, then i wouldn't lie for them and let them back out on the street knowing that they're capable of murder or some other horrible crime. i love my friends, i really do. but if my friend were to commit a crime that has a life sentence attached to it, then that's not something i can condone. lying to save their ass would not be the right thing to do. i'd likely give them some advice free of charge though, which would be to take a plea deal if one is offered.now, if my friend were innocent, then i would testify in the event that my testimony would be helpful, and i'd do whatever i could to keep them from being falsely imprisoned.

question: so, it's basically low-mobility -- it's too heavy and thick for them to effectively pounce or move their necks.  i imagine it's pharamones (s?).   so, who in the pride would lead? would the females give their mates council behind the scenes? (since they talk and such in this book)a @live

(it's like this for a variety of animals, especially hyenas) it's how evolution works. those who are weak will struggle and most likely die, whereas the strong survive - "survival of the fattest". (that's why intruding males who win another male's pride will kill the old male's cubs. they were more fit and won the pride. the cubs have the weak lion's genet, and so they have to go.) anyway, the lioneseses are more likely to follow the more dominant siblings. and as generations pass, these new lioneseses also follow her. but i'm not sure if they follow her like a patriarch. they move their necks just fine. their manes are a dead giveaway, and they're heavy. it's the jumping high enough to climb on prey's back the manes affect. they can still deliver killing bites and such. that's why they hunt small things, or simply scavenge from cheetah, leopard, and hyenas.
